{"lemma":"خُلَّبِ","slug":"خُلَّبِ","root":"خ.ل.ب","root_slug":"خ-ل-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ل-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11203","n11211"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to scratch, to wound by cutting with the nail or the reaping-hook or in another fashion; to sting, to bite"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to snatch, to seize, to clutch, to rend"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to chelate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to allure, to charm, to fascinate, to coax, to captivate with blandishment, to deceive, to hoax"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to chelate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"claw, nail, talon"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَلَبَ (ḵalaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chelation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"case, hull, shell, something which provides less than it suggests, sheet lightning, cloud bearing no rain","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ligneous fibers from which the trunk of a palm is made; the medulla of a palm","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mud that agglutinates easily","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11203","headword_ar":"خِلْبٌ","root":"xlb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZufurN","text_ar":"ظُفُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) used in a general sense [as meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nail"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man, and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talon"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a bird, and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"claw"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a beast: see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mixolabN","text_ar":"مِخْلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaAbN","text_ar":"اَخْلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"only. (TA.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diaphragm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"midriff;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HijaAbu Alqalobi","text_ar":"حِجَابُ القَلْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, L;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HijaAbu","text_ar":"حِجَابُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkabidi","text_ar":"الكَبِدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"partition intervening between the heart and the liver;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"partition between the heart and the belly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj in his “ Khalk el-Insán; ”) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small and thin piece of flesh forming a connection between the ribs"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one side and those of the other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liver"},{"kind":"text","text":"[itself]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziyaAdap","text_ar":"زِيَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAy^idap","text_ar":"زَايِدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a white thin thing adhering to the liver:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain thing in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, the liver, like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gud~ap","text_ar":"غُدَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (JK:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small bone, resembling a man's nail, adhering to one side of the midriff, next the liver."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See 1, in two places. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A friend;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. because he cleaves to another;] as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilomN","text_ar":"خِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK.) ―         -b4-  [And hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilobu nisaA='K","text_ar":"خِلْبُ نِسَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) a phrase like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hidovu nisaA='K","text_ar":"حِدْثُ نِسَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziyru nisaA='K","text_ar":"زِيرُ نِسَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whom women love:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who loves women for the sake of discourse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the sake of vitious"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"immoral conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adultery,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fornication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and whom they love"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in like manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who endeavours to deceive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beguile, women"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with blandishing speech:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 1]: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaAbu","text_ar":"اَخْلَابُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisaA='K","text_ar":"نِسَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisaA='K","text_ar":"نِسَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xulabaA='u","text_ar":"خُلَبَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) the latter [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilobA'u","text_ar":"خِلْباءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] extr. [with respect to rule]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa$oYN","text_ar":"وَشْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of variegated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figured, cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxal~abN","text_ar":"مُخَلَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"radish."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) In a copy of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaHolu","text_ar":"الفَحْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfijolu","text_ar":"الفِجْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broad leaves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the grape-vine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","A","JK","S","TA","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n11211","headword_ar":"خُلَّبٌ","root":"xlb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clouds"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbN","text_ar":"سَحَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that thunder and lighten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"containing no rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereof the lightning flashes slightly, so that one hopes for their raining, but which deceive the expectation, and become dispersed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAbapN","text_ar":"خِلَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the “ deceiving with blandishing speech. ” (IAth.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaroqu Alxul~abi","text_ar":"البَرْقُ الخُلَّبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baroqu xul~abK","text_ar":"بَرْقُ خُلَّبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baroqu Alxul~abi","text_ar":"بَرْقُ الخُلَّبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baroqN","text_ar":"بَرْقٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~abN","text_ar":"خُلَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lightning with which is no rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A;) as though deceiving: (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that excites hope"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and breaks its promise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) Hence the saying, to him who promises and does not fulfil his promise,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~amaA A^anota kabaroqK xul~abK","text_ar":"اـِنَّمَا اَنْتَ كَبَرْقٍ خُلَّبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art only like lightning with which is no rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S.). And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN xul~abN qul~abN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ خُلَّبٌ قُلَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is sharp in intellect, clever, ingenious, skilful, knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}